        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Savannah</placeName>
                <date>March 19. 1839</date>.</p>
            <p>My dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">The arrival of the Schooner Heroine yes=<lb/>terday brought me your
                esteemed favour of the <date>1st</date> instant and<lb/> also the five copies of
                your work, which I shall deliver tomorrow<lb/> to those who subscribed for them, and
                remit you the amount<lb/> as soon as received; the only difficulty I shall have will
                be as to the<lb/> manner of making the remittance, as I could not procure a<lb/>
                draft on your City for so small an amount, however should<lb/> I not be able to do
                so, will send it by <persName>Doctor De LaMotta</persName><lb/> who writes me that
                he will leave <placeName>Charleston</placeName> for the <placeName>north</placeName>
                soon<lb/> after the <date>Passover</date> Holidays;</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Judging from the one or two discourses<lb/> of your collections that
                I have as yet read I am certain I shall be<lb/>
                <sic>be</sic> pleased with them they give an <add>?</add> of what the others
                are<lb/> and <add>?</add> us, do much in diffusing a correct knowledge of<lb/> our
                Holy Religion„ the <sic>exersions</sic> my dear Sir you have and are<lb/> still
                making for that purpose is creditable to yourself and<lb/> desires the support of
                all of us the children of <placeName>Israel</placeName>, you<lb/> shall have mine
                and you will please consider me a standing<lb/> subscriber to all the works you are
                now or may hereafter pub<lb/>lish, the mechanical part of the book is well done, and
                I am<lb/> much pleased with the specimen you have not use of<lb/> your Book of Daily
                Prayers &amp;c be assured I shall use my <sic>exersions</sic><lb/> to get you as
                many subscribers as can be obtained in<lb/> our small community, tho' I cannot
                promise you to<lb/> get many as most of the few who are followers of the</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>religion of their Forefathers are already supplied. I can however<lb/> promise you
                one thing and that is my best <sic>exersions</sic>.<lb/> The weather here is
                delightfully fine, tho' on the <date>4th</date> just Instant<lb/> we witnessed here
                the novel sight of a Snow Storm which<lb/> lasted just sufficiently long to gratify
                those who had never<lb/> before enjoyed the pleasure of a <sic>Slay</sic> ride and
                Snow balling.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">With my best wishes for your success and sincerely
                recipro-<lb/>=cating your kind wishes I remain Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">Your friend &amp; well wisher</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">J. De La Motta Junr.</persName>
            </p>
